MDmodule usage:
	-i <input sequences>
	-w <motif width (default 10)>
	-f <background frequency file>
	-b <background sequence file (default input sequences)>
	-k <background Markov dependency order (default don't specify)>
	-e <expected bases per motif site in the top sequences
	    (will use Bayes motif scoring, don't specify if unkown,
	     which uses Liu motif scoring)>
	-t <number of top sequences to look for candidate motifs (default 10)>
	-s <number of candidate motifs to scan and refine (default 30)>
	-c <number of top sequences to confirm candidate motifs
	    (default whole dataset)>
	-n <number of refinement iterations (default 15)>
	-r <number of top motifs to report at the end (default 5)>
	-a 1 <if want to print out alignments (default just motif matrics)>
	-h <number of site hits (default 300)
	    only works if also specified -a and -x>
	-M <Monte Carlo simulation for motif score distribution
	    (default no Monte Carlo or stat significance score)>
	-C <number of child processes to run Monte Carlo simulation
	    (default one process without no Monte Carlo simulation)>
	-u Motif score distribution mean
	    (default no stat significance score or perform Monte Carlo)>
	-v Motif score distribution mean
	    (default no stat significance score or perform Monte Carlo)>
	-m <predefined motif consensus or degenerate (default do not specify)>
	-p <+/- experiment number (default do not specify)>
	-o <output file (default stdout)>
	-x <matrixscan output file (default no matrixscan)>
	-g 1 <if you don't want to see messages during the run>